@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Pricing - StyloBot";
}

<section class="px-6 py-16">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto text-center">
    <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-primary font-semibold">Simple, transparent pricing</div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-semibold mt-2 leading-tight">
      $100/month per domain. That's it.
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-base-content/80 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <strong>Unlimited requests.</strong> No per-request metering. No traffic surprises. No CDN lock-in.
      Self-hosted at every tier - your traffic never leaves your perimeter.
      The full detection engine is free and open source forever.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-6 flex gap-3 justify-center flex-wrap">
      <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="/portal">Start 30-day free trial</a>
      <a class="btn btn-ghost btn-lg" href="https://github.com/scottgal/stylobot">View source code</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="px-6 pb-12">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">

    <!-- FOSS -->
    <div class="card bg-base-200 p-6 flex flex-col">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Open Source</h2>
      <div class="mt-2"><span class="text-3xl font-bold">$0</span> <span class="text-base-content/60">forever</span></div>
      <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70 mt-3">Fully functional. No license required. No phone-home.</p>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm flex-grow">
        <li>&#10003; All 31 detectors + session vectors</li>
        <li>&#10003; Sub-millisecond fast path (&lt;1ms)</li>
        <li>&#10003; SQLite persistence (zero dependencies)</li>
        <li>&#10003; Local dashboard (read-only)</li>
        <li>&#10003; YAML config (restart to apply)</li>
        <li>&#10003; Local Ollama LLM escalation</li>
        <li>&#10003; Zero PII architecture</li>
        <li>&#10003; Unlimited users (local accounts)</li>
        <li class="text-base-content/40">- Dashboard is view-only</li>
        <li class="text-base-content/40">- Config changes need restart</li>
      </ul>
      <a class="btn btn-outline mt-6" href="https://github.com/scottgal/stylobot">Get the code</a>
    </div>

    <!-- Startup -->
    <div class="card bg-primary/10 ring-2 ring-primary p-6 flex flex-col relative">
      <div class="absolute -top-3 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 text-xs uppercase tracking-widest bg-primary text-primary-content px-3 py-1 rounded-full font-semibold">Most popular</div>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-2">Startup</h2>
      <div class="mt-2">
        <span class="text-3xl font-bold">$100</span>
        <span class="text-base-content/60">/ month per domain</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70 mt-1">Unlimited subdomains included.</p>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm flex-grow">
        <li>&#10003; Everything in Open Source</li>
        <li>&#10003; PostgreSQL persistence</li>
        <li>&#10003; <strong>Live config editor</strong> (no restart)</li>
        <li>&#10003; 5 portal users</li>
        <li>&#10003; 5 per-endpoint policy overrides</li>
        <li>&#10003; Dashboard with write access</li>
        <li>&#10003; OIDC SSO (Keycloak/AzureAD/Okta)</li>
        <li>&#10003; OpenAI + Anthropic LLM providers</li>
        <li>&#10003; Email support</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="mt-4 space-y-1 text-xs text-base-content/50">
        <div>Add-on: <strong>Redis backplane</strong> +$50/mo</div>
        <div>Add-on: <strong>Multi-node / distributed</strong> +$100/mo</div>
      </div>
      <a class="btn btn-primary mt-6" href="/portal">Start 30-day free trial</a>
    </div>

    <!-- Enterprise -->
    <div class="card bg-base-200 p-6 flex flex-col">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Enterprise</h2>
      <div class="mt-2"><span class="text-3xl font-bold">From $1,000</span> <span class="text-base-content/60">/ month</span></div>
      <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70 mt-3">Capability-based. You buy what you need.</p>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm flex-grow">
        <li>&#10003; Everything in Startup</li>
        <li>&#10003; Unlimited users / endpoints / overrides</li>
        <li>&#10003; pgvector HNSW session similarity</li>
        <li>&#10003; Fingerprint approval + locked dimensions</li>
        <li>&#10003; Fleet dashboard (multi-gateway)</li>
        <li>&#10003; Kubernetes operator</li>
        <li>&#10003; SAML 2.0 + SCIM provisioning</li>
        <li>&#10003; Distributed YARP pipeline coordination</li>
        <li>&#10003; Scheduled reports + compliance exports</li>
        <li>&#10003; Private LLM integration</li>
        <li>&#10003; SLA + dedicated support engineers</li>
      </ul>
      <a class="btn btn-outline mt-6" href="/contact">Talk to us</a>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<!-- Why StyloBot vs the alternatives -->
<section class="px-6 py-12 bg-base-200">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-center mb-2">How we compare</h2>
    <p class="text-center text-base-content/60 mb-6 text-sm">We're new - but we're also the only self-hosted full bot management platform at this price point.</p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="table text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Vendor</th>
            <th>Starting price</th>
            <th>Mid-market</th>
            <th>Self-hosted?</th>
            <th>Open source?</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="font-semibold bg-primary/5">
            <td>StyloBot</td>
            <td class="text-primary font-bold">$0 (FOSS) / $100/mo</td>
            <td>$100 - $1,000/mo</td>
            <td class="text-success font-bold">Always</td>
            <td class="text-success font-bold">Full engine</td>
          </tr>
          <tr><td>CrowdSec</td><td>$0 OSS</td><td>$900+/mo (blocklists)</td><td class="text-success">Yes</td><td>Partial</td></tr>
          <tr><td>AWS WAF Bot Control</td><td>$10/mo + per-request</td><td>$100+/mo</td><td class="text-error">No (AWS only)</td><td class="text-error">No</td></tr>
          <tr><td>CHEQ</td><td>$149/mo</td><td>$999+/mo</td><td class="text-error">No</td><td class="text-error">No</td></tr>
          <tr><td>DataDome</td><td>$2,990/mo</td><td>$5,990+/mo</td><td class="text-error">No</td><td class="text-error">No</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Cloudflare Bot Mgmt</td><td>$3,000/mo (Enterprise)</td><td>$5K - $15K/mo</td><td class="text-error">No (CDN lock-in)</td><td class="text-error">No</td></tr>
          <tr><td>HUMAN Security</td><td>$5,000+/mo</td><td>$10K - $30K/mo</td><td class="text-error">No</td><td class="text-error">No</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Akamai Bot Manager</td><td>$5,000+/mo</td><td>$10K - $50K/mo</td><td class="text-error">No (CDN lock-in)</td><td class="text-error">No</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <div class="text-xs text-base-content/40 mt-2">
        Pricing as of April 2026. Sources: vendor pricing pages, G2, public documentation.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Trial -->
<section class="px-6 py-12">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">30-day free trial. No credit card.</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-base-content/80 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      Full Startup feature set for 30 days. After the trial, commercial features switch to
      <strong>logging-only mode</strong> - your detection keeps running, your gateways keep
      protecting traffic. We never turn off protection because of a billing issue.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-6 flex gap-3 justify-center flex-wrap">
      <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="/portal">Start the trial</a>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-4 text-xs text-base-content/50">
      Ed25519-signed license. No phone-home. Validates locally against the vendor public key.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="px-6 py-12 bg-base-200">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">FAQ</h2>

    <div class="mt-6 space-y-6">
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold">Is the open source version really fully functional?</h3>
        <p class="text-base-content/80 mt-1 text-sm">
          Yes. All 31 detectors, session vectors, per-transition timing analysis, local dashboard,
          SQLite persistence, Ollama LLM escalation. The commercial version adds PostgreSQL,
          live config editing, and fleet management - but the detection engine is identical.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold">What does "$100/month per domain" include?</h3>
        <p class="text-base-content/80 mt-1 text-sm">
          One domain and all its subdomains. <code>example.com</code>, <code>api.example.com</code>,
          <code>staging.example.com</code> - all covered under one license. No per-request charges,
          no traffic limits, no bandwidth metering.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold">What happens after the trial?</h3>
        <p class="text-base-content/80 mt-1 text-sm">
          Commercial features switch to logging-only mode. The live config editor becomes read-only,
          PostgreSQL persistence stops writing new events (existing data stays), but
          <strong>detection never stops</strong>. Your gateways keep protecting traffic using
          SQLite and YAML config - exactly like the FOSS version.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold">Why is StyloBot so much cheaper than DataDome or Cloudflare?</h3>
        <p class="text-base-content/80 mt-1 text-sm">
          Those vendors run SaaS infrastructure at global scale - PoPs, CDN edge nodes, SOC teams.
          StyloBot runs in <em>your</em> infrastructure. You bring the compute; we bring the
          detection intelligence. No infrastructure markup, no per-request tax.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold">Can I upgrade mid-month?</h3>
        <p class="text-base-content/80 mt-1 text-sm">
          Yes. Upgrade from Startup to Enterprise, add Redis or multi-node - changes are
          prorated. Your license token is re-issued immediately via the portal.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
